The paper introduces a logic that extends first-order logic with counting and numerical predicates, making it relevant to the areas of logic (cs.LO) and databases (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the locality of formulas and its applications, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC). The model checking and query evaluation problems mentioned in the abstract are typical problems in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper's focus on counting and numerical predicates suggests that it may also be relevant to the area of data structures (cs.DS).
